cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spectrum sensing and traffic adaptation in cognitive networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the estimation and aggregation of spectrum occupancy information. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a decentralized approach for network control. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible as the paper mentions throughput optimization. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also possible as the paper proposes an agglomerative clustering algorithm for designing the aggregation tree.
